    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1866-07-16T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1866-07-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="131" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d131">
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Extract.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                                King</persName>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 40.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State,</hi>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington,</hi>
                        </placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1866-07-16">
                            <hi rend="italic">July</hi> 16, 1866</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: In further acknowledgment of your despatch
                            of the 23d of June, I have to inform you that I have laid before the
                            Secretary of War the letter which accompanies it, and which was written
                            by Henri de St. Marie on the 21st of June last.</p>
                <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Rufus King,</hi> Esq., <hi rend="italic">&amp;c., &amp;c., &amp;c.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
